 as a concert pianist and dancer, soloing at Carnegie Hall and recording Saint-Saens with the Philadelphia Orchestra. In 1932 she founded the Montgomery Ballet and ran it as director and choreographer."},{"category":"legacy","header":"Her last travel lecture, the day she died","body":"Widowed in 1964, she made fourteen journeys through South Asia and photographed thousands of scenes. She gave travel lectures for decades, delivering her final one on the day she died in 1995."}],"slug":"mary-binney-montgomery-wheeler-hd6147"},"HD6148":{"id":"HD6148","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":11},"gender":"male","tags":["navy","wwii"],"parents":{"father_id":"I01686","mother_id":"HD6144"},"birth":{"year":1911,"month":5,"day":7,"state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1997,"month":3,"day":14,"city":"Villanova","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM790"},"bio":{"display_name":"Robert Alexander Arnulph Montgomery"},"number_of_marriages":3,"education":[{"institution_id":"INST173","type":"graduation"},{"institution_id":"INST002","type":"graduation"}],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST173","relationship":"alumnus"},{"institution_id":"INST002","relationship":"alumnus"}],"career":[{"role":"General Partner","organization":"Montgomery Scott & Co."},{"role":"Commissioner","organization":"Radnor Township Board of Commissioners"}],"military_service":[{"war":"World War II","war_id":"WAR008","branch":"United States Naval Reserve","rank":"Lieutenant Commander","years":"1942-1945","notes":"Merchant Marine procurement in Philadelphia; senior watch officer aboard USS General E. T. Collins in the Pacific."}],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM140","landmark_blurb":"He lived his whole life on the Ardrossan estate, hosting Presidents Ford and Bush."}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01690","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1933,"end_type":"divorce","end_year":1948,"children_ids":["HD6152","HD6153"]},{"spouse_id":"X03169","marriage_number":2,"children_ids":[]},{"spouse_id":"I01691","marriage_number":3,"date_year":1972,"children_ids":[]}],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"military","header":"A Navy officer in the wartime Pacific","body":"He volunteered for the Naval Reserve in the Second World War, handling Merchant Marine procurement and serving as a watch officer aboard a transport in the Pacific. He came home to the family brokerage."},{"category":"business","header":"He helped found the family brokerage at Ardrossan","body":"With his father he helped build Montgomery Scott & Co., staying a partner until 1989. He spent his whole life on the Ardrossan estate."},{"category":"character","header":"He hosted two presidents at Ardrossan","body":"A Republican and Radnor township commissioner, he welcomed Presidents Ford and Bush to the estate. He collected firearms and African memorabilia from his travels."}],"slug":"robert-alexander-arnulph-montgomery-hd6148"},"HD6149":{"id":"HD6149","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":11},"gender":"female","parents":{"father_id":"I01686","mother_id":"HD6144"},"birth":{"year":1912,"month":12,"day":28,"city":"Villanova","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1981,"month":9,"day":25,"state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM790"},"bio":{"display_name":"Charlotte Ives Montgomery","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781040791/65115305_4c7ca017-e5ae-4bbb-a856-45252333be62-resized_qogtb5.jpg"},"number_of_marriages":1,"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM140","landmark_blurb":"Born just as the family moved in, she returned to her childhood bedroom at Ardrossan."}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01692","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1943,"children_ids":[]}],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"character","header":"A debutante who flew her own plane","body":"Fearless and funny, Charlotte Ives earned a pilot's license and flew her own WACO biplane while her peers went to dances. She was a nationally ranked horsewoman with a gift for animals."},{"category":"family","header":"She chose her childhood bedroom at Ardrossan","body":"Late in life she sold her Carolina home and returned to Ardrossan, taking her old third-floor bedroom over any other. She brought her dogs and cats with her."}],"slug":"charlotte-ives-montgomery-hd6149"},"HD6145":{"id":"HD6145","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":10},"gender":"male","parents":{"father_id":"HD6140","mother_id":"I01683"},"birth":{"year":1883,"month":8,"day":10,"city":"Newport","state":"Rhode Island","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1947,"month":1,"day":8,"city":"Abington","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"bio":{"display_name":"George Frederick Tyler II","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781045305/49371229_c83aecc5-d08e-4210-ae0f-f539f130718d_mxctqd.jpg","suffix":"II"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01685","marriage_number":1,"children_ids":["HD6175","HD6176","HD6177"],"date_year":1905,"date_month":4,"date_day":27}],"tags":["banker","farmer","wwi","philanthropy"],"career":[{"role":"Banker","organization":"Philadelphia"},{"role":"State Commander","organization":"American Legion (Pennsylvania)"}],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM141","landmark_blurb":"Built the French-Norman country house 'Indian Council Rock' on his Bucks County estate."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"character","header":"A banker who would rather be on safari","body":"Heir to a Philadelphia banking family, George Tyler spent his leisure on big-game safaris, mountain climbing, and yacht racing. After the First World War he turned increasingly toward farming and philanthropy."},{"category":"legacy","header":"His country estate is now a state park","body":"He built a French-Norman house called Indian Council Rock on a sprawling Bucks County farm. The land today forms Tyler State Park and the campus of Bucks County Community College."},{"category":"character","header":"The war pulled him out of his cocoon","body":"By his grandson's account, the First World War and surviving the 1918 pandemic transformed him from an insular Philadelphia aristocrat into a public-minded benefactor."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"cousin_marriage","related_id":"HD2426","display_label":"saw her daughter Constance wed his son Sidney Tyler"},{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X03172","display_label":"was the coal-tar magnate father of his wife Stella"},{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X03173","display_label":"was the mother of his wife Stella the sculptor"}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM798"},"slug":"george-frederick-tyler-ii-hd6145"},"I01685":{"id":"I01685","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1884,"month":3,"day":16,"city":"Philadelphia","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1963,"month":11,"day":2,"city":"Springfield Township","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"bio":{"display_name":"Stella Van Tuyl Elkins Tyler","photo_url":"htt